The storytelling prowess of Supermassive Games meets the Dead by Daylight universe in a haunting horror game that won‚Äôt soon be forgotten.

The shadow of Frank Stone looms over Cedar Hills, a town forever altered by his violent past. As a group of young friends are about to discover, Stone‚Äôs blood-soaked legacy cuts deep, leaving scars across families, generations, and the very fabric of reality itself.  

In the depths of an Oregon steel mill, the gruesome crimes of a sadistic killer spawn horrors beyond comprehension. Delve into the mystery of Cedar Hills alongside an original cast of characters bound together on a twisted journey where nothing is quite as it seems.  

Every decision you make shapes the story and impacts the fate of the characters within it. Brimming with emotional gut-punches and high-stakes horror, discover how a simple decision can become a truly heart-wrenching dilemma.

For those who find comfort in the unknown, and glee in the grotesque, Supermassive Games‚Äô cinematic storytelling brings new levels of emotion, immersion, and intensity to this darkly rich universe.

 Severe storms that tore through central Tennessee killed six people Saturday and sent about two dozen to the hospital as homes and businesses were damaged in multiple cities.

Three people, including a child, were killed after an apparent tornado struck Montgomery County north of Nashville near the Kentucky state line, county officials said in a news release. And the Nashville Emergency Operation Center said in a post on a social media account that three people were killed by severe storms there. Montgomery County officials said another 23 there were treated for injuries at hospitals.

description:
Welcome to the ULTIMATE petrol vs electric drag race! 

We‚Äôve got our hands on the all-new Tesla Cybertruck, and it‚Äôs lining up alongside the a Lamborghini Urus! But which will come out on top - petrol, or electric? 

Well, let‚Äôs check out the stats. Starting with the Cybertruck, it rolls up equipped with three electric motors, and they combine to produce 845hp and 930Nm of torque. The starting price of the dual-motor edition is around $49,000, but for this tri-motor Cyberbeast edition, it‚Äôll cost you around $96,000! In terms of weight, the Cybertruck tips the scales at just over 3 tonnes. It also has a top speed of 130mph. 

Then we have the Lambo. It‚Äôs packing a 4-litre twin-turbo V8 under the bonnet, and this can produce 650hp and 850Nm of torque. Power is sent to all four wheels via an 8-speed torque converter gearbox, and it‚Äôs a whole lot lighter than the Tesla, tipping the scales at 2,200kg. It also has a much bigger top speed, coming in at 190mph. 

So the Cybertruck has the Urus beat when it comes to performance stats, but will the extra weight drag it down? There‚Äôs only one way to find out for sure‚Ä¶ LET‚ÄôS RACE!

description:
In this video, I measure a wave of electricity traveling down a wire, and answer the question - how does electricity know where to go? How does "electricity" "decide" where electrons should be moving in wires, and how long does that process take? Spoiler alert - very fast!

I've been very excited about this project for a while - it was a lot of work to figure out a reliable way to make these measurements, but I've learned SO much by actually watching waves travel down wires, and I hope you do too!

There will be a Q&A about this video posted in a few weeks on the second channel, and if you head over there right now, you'll see two direct follow ups to this video with experimental details, and a section about "impedance matching" that was cut from this script.

description:
Since 1927, TIME has chosen a Person of the Year, the editors‚Äô assessment of the individual who most shaped the headlines over the previous 12 months, for better or for worse. 

As a tradition, Person of the Year springs from the Great Man Theory of history, a belief that individuals have the power to transform society. The selections over the years have tended to follow certain patterns. The person chosen has typically been a ruler over traditional domains of power. He‚Äîand yes, usually it has been a ‚Äúhe‚Äù‚Äîis very often a politician or a titan of industry. Fourteen U.S. Presidents, five leaders of Russia or the Soviet Union, and three Popes have all been recognized.

And yet the person whose singular influence was revealed throughout 2023 has held none of these roles‚Äîor anything remotely similar. Every year contains light and dark; 2023 was a year with significant shares of darkness. In a divided world, where too many institutions are failing, Taylor Swift found a way to transcend borders and be a source of light. No one else on the planet today can move so many people so well. Achieving this feat is something we often chalk up to the alignments of planets and fates, but giving too much credit to the stars ignores her skill and her power. 

Taylor Swift is TIME‚Äôs 2023 Person of the Year.

The film is produced by Mary Parent, Alex Garcia, Eric Mcleod, Thomas Tull, Jon Jashni and Brian Rogers. Once again, Wingard is collaborating with director of photography Ben Seresin (‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù ‚ÄúWorld War Z‚Äù), production designer Tom Hammock (‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù ‚ÄúX,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Guest‚Äù), editor Josh Schaeffer (‚ÄúGodzilla vs. Kong,‚Äù ‚ÄúMolly‚Äôs Game‚Äù), costume designer Emily Seresin (‚ÄúThe Invisible Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúTop of the Lake‚Äù). Anxiety anecdote: 

This one took about two months to make. Lots of that time was faffing around with a Word document, not even sure what the point of the script was, but anyhow - today, very excited to be finally uploading and rid of the thing, there I was doing a bit of last minute polishing in the video editor and suddenly I notice I've deleted half the video in the timeline. Just gone. I reload the old save file but it's too late, I've written over it already. About a month of work gone in three seconds of mis-clicking. I'm not sure how far back in the day I made the mistake and did I mention that the file is so large now that the undo function locks the video editor up almost every time? There's only one option left: tentatively keep hitting undo and just pray this doesn't lock the editor up otherwise ALL GONE, and just pray the buffer remembers far back enough to restore the sequence I deleted otherwise ALL GONE. There I sat for thirty minutes hitting ctrl-z as gently as I could, sweat dripping from my furrowed brow, even the mice who live in the walls of my apartment coming out to watch and bite their fingernails or claws or whatever it is mice have, their cheese untouched, their traps empty.... Anyway everything was fine even if I almost soiled myself - the undo function worked and I briefly felt good about living again for the first time in ten years. I am an idiot. Please don't be an idiot like me - back stuff up, I beg ye.

description:
Cyberpunk 2077: Ultimate Edition is out now on Xbox Series X|S, PlayStation 5, and PC! ü•≥

Grab your digital or physical copy and experience every story Night City has to offer. ‚ú®

https://cyberpunk.net/buy

Cyberpunk 2077: Ultimate Edition is an open-world, action-adventure RPG containing every story set in Night City, featuring a host of memorable characters including rebellious rockerboy Johnny Silverhand (played by Keanu Reeves) and veteran secret agent Solomon Reed (played by Idris Elba). Play as V, a cyberpunk mercenary, and take on the most powerful forces of the city in a fight for glory and survival. Dive into the base game, its critically acclaimed spy-thriller expansion Phantom Liberty, and experience the game-changing Update 2.0 ‚Äî all in one package. Legends are made here. What will yours be?

Descriptive text:

A trailer made up of dynamic cuts between gameplay footage from Cyberpunk 2077 and Phantom Liberty interspersed with live-action scenes of actors Keanu Reeves and Idris Elba.

Game footage shows the silhouette of Solomon Reed, a dark-skinned man in a brown leather trench coat, shooting a gun at an unseen enemy. Soldiers jump out of an AV into a burning building. An explosion throws President Myers, a white woman in a pantsuit, to the ground. Trauma Team employees defibrillate a woman. A police car explodes.

An AV flies over a sweeping expanse of Night City. A black title card reads: ‚ÄúAn Unprecedented Revival. The Guardian.‚Äù An enormous pyramid-shaped building glows in Dogtown. In an alleyway, a group of women beat up a man who is lying on the ground. A black title card reads: ‚ÄúAn Unforgettable Open-World Experience. Polygon.‚Äù

Inside of a club, Idris Elba wears a black suit jacket and walks forward as he speaks to the camera. In the game, a heavily armed MaxTac unit drops onto the ground from an AV. A MaxTac agent points a gun at V. The trunk of a car is opened to reveal an arsenal of weapons. A red-haired woman winks at V over a roulette table.

Keanu Reeves speaks. In the game, characters dance on a crowded dance floor. Four musicians stand on stage as the audience applauds. A rock band plays on a cramped stage with the Samurai logo behind them. A blue-haired woman looks up at V.

Keanu Reeves walks backwards as he speaks. In Cyberpunk 2077, an intimidating cyborg soldier with red eyes walks past. Dogtown leader Kurt Hansen is trailed by two loyal soldiers. A man covered in implants and with a cybernetic light in his forehead gestures. A woman climbs out of a storage container.

Idris Elba strides forward in the club. In the game, V pierces an enemy‚Äôs chest with two electric blades then knocks another enemy back with a shotgun blast. V drives a sleek Quadra car through Night City streets. A masked enemy swings two glowing red blades at V.

Armed forces exit an AV, guns aimed forward. A powerful pistol blast explodes a motorcycle in mid-air. A silver-skinned woman floats aboveground in a holographic light show. V faces down various enemies and a large battle tank.

The Cyberpunk 2077: Ultimate Edition logo glitches into view. Below are the words ‚ÄúBuy Now‚Äù. The game is available for Xbox Series X|S, PlayStation 5, and PC.
title: Cyberpunk 2077: Ultimate Edition ‚Äî Official Launch Trailer

On satellite imagery, we spotted a village inside a strange crater in Madagascar. We set out to learn how it got there.

Subscribe to our channel! http://goo.gl/0bsAjO

Right in the center of the island nation of Madagascar there‚Äôs a strange, almost perfectly circular geological structure. It covers a bigger area than the city of Paris ‚Äî and at first glance, it looks completely empty. But right in the center of that structure, there‚Äôs a single, isolated village: a few dozen houses, some fields of crops, and dirt roads stretching out in every direction. 

When we first saw this village on Google Earth, its extreme remoteness fascinated us. Was the village full of people? How did they wind up there? And what did life look like in such a strange geography? To find out, we teamed up with a local team in Madagascar and fell down a rabbit hole of geology and mapping along the way. It‚Äôs a story of how continental shifts and volcanic geology came together to form a place for a group of people to call home. 

We got to talk with a lot of experts along the way to make this piece. Here are links to some of their work:

Here is some of Michel J√©brak‚Äôs research on the Richat structure: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/32048440_Resolving_the_Richat_enigma_Doming_and_hydrothermal_karstification_above_an_alkaline_complex

Here is Ndivhuwo Cecilia Mukosi‚Äôs original paper on the Ambohiby Complex: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/318723814_Petrogenesis_of_the_Ambohiby_Complex_Madagascar_and_the_role_of_the_Marion_Hotspot_plume

We also spoke with Stian Rice, author of Famine in the Remaking, who helped us understand more about the history of agriculture in Madagascar:  https://gjia.georgetown.edu/2022/01/24/madagascars-famine-is-more-than-climate-change/

Check out Stian‚Äôs book on famine and food systems: https://wvupressonline.com/node/831

Norman Thomas Uphoff at Cornell‚Äôs SRI International Network also shared more about agricultural systems and innovation: http://sri.ciifad.cornell.edu/

Correction: At 2:52, we mistakenly labeled Lucienne Wilm√© as a professor of geology at the University of Florida. In fact, she is a national coordinator of the Madagascar Program at the World Resources Institute.
